This paper deals with the problem of nearest neighbor search, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and is relevant to several subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of locality-sensitive hash functions is a common technique in these subfields to solve the nearest neighbor search problem efficiently, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
